Create columns using merge, conditional and split columns. 3


In this step the FactTable will be modified to create necessary columns for the Dahsboard. This will mostly take place in Power Query.


 


 

Step 3.1 – Opening Power Query and adding an index column.

1. Click on Transform Data located in the Home tab in the Queries menu. This will open Power Query Editor.

2. Go to the Add Column tab. In the General menu, click on the downward arrow (?) and select from 1.

3. A new column was added. Right click on the header and select Move -> To the beginning.

4. Now rename the column To ShootingID.

  

 

Step 3.2 – Rename columns and select the appropriate datatype.

1. Rename the columns with a double click on the header. Use a meaningful name and proper format.

2. To change the Data type, select the column that needs a data type change.

3. Go to the Transform tab. From the Any column menu choose the new format.

For the visual displaying the weapons used in the shootings, new columns must be created. These columns will be created in the next steps.

 

Step 3.3 – Merging columns

The table needs to have one value per row for each column. In the WeaponType column, some rows have multiple values. In this step these values will be separated into their own row.

1. Start by selecting both columns, WeaponType and WeaponDetails.

2. Click on the Add Column Tab.

3. Find in the From Text menu the option Merge Columns

4. Choose space as separator.

5. Assign the name to the new column. In this case MergedWeaponTypeDetails.

 

 



Step 3.4 – Creating Conditional Columns

This step will create 3 columns needed for a visual.

Columns: Handgun Rifle and Shotgun


Each word will have 4 combinations. Uppercase singular, Uppercase plural, Lowercase singular, Lowercase plural

For example Handgun --> Handgun, Handguns, handgun, handguns

In this first Conditional column, these is needed for 3 words.

Words: Handgun, Pistol, Revolver


1. Select the column MergedWeaponTypeDetails.

2. Click on the Add Column Tab

3. From the General menu, select Conditional Column.

4. A new window will appear. Input the following values. This will create the column Handgun.






5. Repeat the same steps to create the columns Rifle and Shotgun.


  


 

 

 

 Step 3.5 – Merge the 3 columns into one.

1. Start by selecting the 3 columns to merge (Handgun, Rifle, and Shotgun)

2. Go to the Add Column Tab

3. Select Merge Columns from the From Text menu.

4. Choose space as from the separator menu.

5. Assign the new name to the column. In this case WeaponIUsed.

 

 



Step 3.6 – Replace blank values with Unknown.

1. Select the column WeaponUsed

2. Go to the Transform tab.

3. Select the icon Replace Values.

4. Leave blank the field Value to Find

5. Type Unknown in the field Replace With

6. Click Ok.
